ics, Context and Culture demonstrates the potential of corpus linguistic methods for investigating language patterns across a range of contexts. Organised in three sections, the chapters range from detailed case studies on lexico-grammatical patterns to fundamental discussions of meaning as part of the ‘discourse, contexts and cultures’ theme. The final part on ‘learner contexts’ specifically emphasises the need for mixed-method approaches and the consideration of pedagogical implications for real world contexts. Beyond its contribution to current debates in the field, this edited volume indicates new directions in cross-disciplinary work.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aDiskursanalyse. 4aKorpus (Linguistik). 4aKorpuslinguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aCorpus (Linguistics).  aCorpus Linguistics.  aDiscourse Analysis.1 aBaker, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBusse, Beatrix, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeuber, Dagmar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDirdal, Hildegunn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarretson, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraedler, Anne-Line, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGregory, Ian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHartmann, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasselgård, Hilde, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHänsel, Eva Canan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaunisto, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 